<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Bodhidharma#CITEREFRed_Pine1989" title="Bodhidharma">Red Pine (1989</a>:3), emphasis added.<br />
<a href="/wiki/Bodhidharma#CITEREFBroughton1999" title="Bodhidharma">Broughton (1999</a>:9) offers a more literal rendering of the key phrase 凝住壁觀 (<i>níngzhù bìguān</i>) as "[who] in a coagulated state abides in wall-examining".</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> e.g., <a href="/wiki/Keizan" title="Keizan">Keizan</a>, <i><a href="http://www.wwzc.org/translations/denkoroku.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.wwzc.org/translations/denkoroku.htm" rel="nofollow">Denkoroku</a></i>;<br />
